    "recap_headline": "Texas A&M",
    "recap_text": "BRYAN-COLLEGE STATION\u00a0\u2013\nNo. 23 Texas A&M downed Texas State, 9-6, behind eight hits and three home runs Tuesday night from Olsen Field at Blue Bell Park.\nAfter falling behind, 4-0, in the second inning, the Aggies (17-3) spotted seven runs in the fourth to claim the lead.\nChris Hacopian\nput the Maroon & White on the board with a solo shot to left field. On a full count with two outs and the bases loaded,\nBoston Kellner\nput the Aggies within reach with a two-RBI single to left.\nGavin Grahovac\nlined a single up the middle to plate two runs and put the home team in front.\nCaden Sorrell\nput a cap on the frame with a frozen rope two-run homer to left field, leaving the bat at 112 miles per hour with an 18-degree launch angle.\nThe Bobcats (12-8) answered in the fifth inning with a two spot to make it a one-run ballgame. In the seventh inning, Sorrell drove his second long ball of the game to the opposite field, giving the Maroon & White a 9-6 advantage.\nCole Hubert\nwas tabbed the starter for the first time in his career. The freshman went three up, three down with two strikeouts in the first inning, but could only manage one out in the second before being relieved.\nGavin Lyons\n(2-0) was the first out of the bullpen for the Aggies. The sophomore right-hander earned the win and tossed 3.1 innings, allowing two runs on two hits and striking out three.\nJuan Vargas\nwas called upon with two outs in the fifth inning, inducing a groundout on one pitch. The Panama City, Panama, native threw 2.0 innings without allowing a baserunner and struck out a pair.\nEthan Darden\nentered in the seventh, giving the home team 1.1 scoreless innings of relief.\nClayton Freshcorn\nearned his fourth save of the year, recording the last three outs and punching out one batter.\nTOP PLAYERS\nCaden Sorrell\n\u2013 2-for-4, 2 R, 4 RBI, 2 HR\nGavin Grahovac\n\u2013 2-for-3, 2 R, 2 RBI, 1 BB\nChris Hacopian\n\u2013 1-for-4, 1 R, 1 RBI, 1 HR\nBoston Kellner\n\u2013 1-for-3, 1 R, 2 RBI\nJuan Vargas\n\u2013 2.0 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 0 BB, 2 K\nSCORING SUMMARY\nT2 | Manny Salas and Ethan Farris led off with consecutive singles. Jaquae Stewart drove a deep single to center field that plated Salas. Chase Mora singled down the right field line to bring Farris home and advance Stewart to third. Brady Boles walked to load the bases and Jackson Cotton grounded out to first base to plate a run. The Bobcats scored their fourth run on a Rashawn Galloway infield single. A&M 0, Texas State 4.\nB4 | Hacopian drilled a home run to left field to put the Aggies on the board.\nWesley Jordan\nfollowed with a single up the middle. With two outs,\nTerrence Kiel II\nand\nBear Harrison\ndrew consecutive walks to load the bases. Kellner singled to left field, plating two runs, and advanced to second on the throw. Grahovac singled up the middle to score Kellner. Sorrell added the final touch of the frame with a two-run shot to right field. A&M 7, Texas State 4.\nT5 | Galloway walked and scored on a Dawson Park double to right-center field. Salas grounded out to first base, advancing Park to third. The run scored on a Farris groundout to the shortstop. A&M 7, Texas State 6.\nB7 | Grahovac singled to left field and Sorrell blasted his second home run of the contest to extend the Aggie edge. A&M 9, Texas State 6.\nGAME NOTES\nTuesday's midweek marked the 65th meeting between the clubs. With the win, the Aggies lead the series 50-15.\nBlue Bell Park held 5,749 fans for the contest.\nSorrell's second home run of the game marked the 34th of his career in the Maroon & White which ranks in a tie for eighth all-time in program history.\nHis four-RBI performance is his team-best 10th multi-RBI game of the year. Additionally, his two-homer performance is his third this season and the sixth of his career.\nKellner and Kiel have reached base safely in all 20 games this season.\nGrahovac and Sorrell extended their on-base streaks to 14 games.\nHubert made his first career start and matched a season high with two strikeouts.\nHacopian's home run in the fourth inning was his first at Blue Bell Park.\nFreshcorn's save was his fourth this season and the sixth of his career.\nUP NEXT\nTexas A&M gears up for a three-game set with No. 7 Georgia at Blue Bell Park, beginning Friday, March 20, at 6 p.m.\nFollow the Aggies\nVisit for more information on Texas A&M baseball. Fans can keep up to date with the A&M baseball team on\u00a0Facebook, Instagram\u00a0and X by following @aggiebaseball."
  },
